'''Dimitris Gogos''' ({{langx|el|Δημήτρης Γκόγκος}}; 28 February 1903{{spaced ndash}}18 November 1985) was one of the most influential singers and composers of [[rebetiko]] music. Also called '''Bayianteras''' ({{langx|el|Μπαγιαντέρας}}), a nickname that was given to him in 1925 for covering and playing in [[bouzouki]] [[Emmerich Kálmán]]'s [[operetta]], ''[[Die Bajadere (operetta)|Die Bajadere]]'', Gogos wrote songs that met great success and popularity in occupied [[Greece]].

